verbose_text: The prototype antidepressants discovered in 1950s were an inhibitor of monoamine transporters (imipr-amine) and monoamine oxidase inhibitor (iproniazid), both of which increases neurotransmission of monoamines; serotonin, noradrenaline, and dopamine.
evidence: monoamine oxidase inhibitor (iproniazid), both of which increases neurotransmission of monoamines; serotonin, noradrenaline
